# Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env` and update the values according to your setup.

```env
# Application
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000
BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:3000
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/bus-express

# JWT Configuration
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-this-in-production
JWT_EXPIRE=7d
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your-super-secret-refresh-key-change-this-in-production
JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRE=30d

# Email Configuration
FROM_EMAIL=noreply@busexpress.com
FROM_NAME=Bus Express
EMAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
EMAIL_PORT=587
EMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASS=your-app-password
SENDGRID_API_KEY=your-sendgrid-api-key

# OTP Configuration
OTP_EXPIRE_MINUTES=10
OTP_LENGTH=6

# Password Reset
PASSWORD_RESET_EXPIRE_MINUTES=60

# Google OAuth
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret
GOOGLE_CALLBACK_URL=http://localhost:3000/auth/google/callback

# Rate Limiting
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=900000
RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS=100

# File Upload
MAX_FILE_SIZE=5242880
UPLOAD_PATH=uploads/
ALLOWED_FILE_TYPES=image/jpeg,image/png,image/gif,image/webp

# CORS
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000

# Stripe Payment
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=your-stripe-secret-key
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your-stripe-publishable-key
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your-stripe-webhook-secret
STRIPE_CURRENCY=usd
```

## Required Variables

- `MONGODB_URI`: MongoDB connection string
- `JWT_SECRET`: Secret key for JWT tokens
- `JWT_REFRESH_SECRET`: Secret key for refresh tokens

## Optional Variables

- `EMAIL_*`: Email service configuration
- `GOOGLE_*`: Google OAuth configuration
- `STRIPE_*`: Stripe payment configuration
- `CORS_ORIGIN`: CORS origin (defaults to *)
- `RATE_LIMIT_*`: Rate limiting configuration
- `UPLOAD_PATH`: File upload directory
- `MAX_FILE_SIZE`: Maximum file size in bytes
